    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your<strong> tuna</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tuna</strong>, <strong>grated cheese </strong>and <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(save the rest for later!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tuna filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>tuna filling</strong> between your<strong> tortillas</strong>, covering only half</p><p>Fold each tortilla over and press down firmly so you're left with 2 half moon-shaped quesadillas per person \u2013 these are your <strong>quesadillas</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pan over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add 2 <strong>quesadillas</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-4 min or until slightly brown</p><p>Carefully flip the quesadillas with a spatula (you might need to use your hand for extra support) and cook for another 2-4 min on the other side \u2013 these are your <strong>tuna melt quesadillas</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the quesadillas cook, combine the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and <strong>remaining chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>in a small bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with a little <strong>salt </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-melt-quesadillas-with-chipotle-salsa/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>tuna melt quesadillas </strong>to a clean board and cut in half</p><p>Serve the <strong>tuna melt quesadillas </strong>with the <strong>chipotle salsa </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Dress the salad with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>white wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
